	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001268_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 28 top left--><!--hand 02 63318 top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right">Kendal</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">2 March</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1858</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Taylor</persName></p>
<lb/><p>In talking 
<lb/>over matters here 
<lb/>with my friends 
<lb/>the idea has 
<lb/>sprung up in 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001268_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>mind that if 
<lb/>you could get 
<lb/>a statement 
<lb/>on paper from 
<lb/><persName>D<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Tidman</persName>
<lb/>that I could 
<lb/>shew to <persName>Thompson</persName>
<lb/>it would be 
<lb/>more satisfactory 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001268_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>than a mere verbal 
<lb/>assurance such 
<lb/>as you got. If 
<lb/>you would not 
<lb/>think this too much 
<lb/>trouble I should feel 
<lb/>obliged.</p>
<lb/><p>When I came home 
<lb/><persName>Tidman</persName><hi rend="underline">said</hi> the 
<lb/>same thing to me 
<lb/>but here <persName>Thompson</persName>
<lb/>sends the letter you 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001268_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<lb/>saw through the 
<lb/>Mission House 
<lb/>and all their 
<lb/>letters on business 
<lb/>go through each 
<lb/>others hands open 
<lb/>I have no assurance 
<lb/>to shew <persName>Thompson</persName>
<lb/>at present.</p>
<lb/><p>I am at 
<lb/>Liverpool tomorrow 
<lb/>I wrote you today this 
<lb/>is an afterthought</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
			
